here, a tooltip will show up on the right that 
represents, or that shows, that year of the 
point selected and then the proportion of 
area deforested for that year.

11
00:01:09.600 --> 00:01:14.700 align:center
And then, whatever point the user selects is 
how the three visualizations are linked.

12
00:01:14.700 --> 00:01:20.001 align:center
And so, if we scroll down on this page, on the 
left side is the first plot of Visual Encoding 2,

13
00:01:20.001 --> 00:01:27.001 align:center
which is a scatterplot with 200 points 
representative of the percentage of the 
Amazon Rainforest remaining in a certain 
year.

14
00:01:27.300 --> 00:01:36.700 align:center
And so, in this case with 2001, uh, all the 
green points represent the proportion of the 
forest that's left, so, in this case, 91.5%.

15
00:01:36.700 --> 00:01:43.001 align:center
And the brown dots represent the proportion 
of the forest that's been deforested, so, uh, 
8.5%.

16
00:01:43.001 --> 00:01:51.800 align:center
And this same data is portrayed in the pie 
chart to the right, which shows the percent 
deforested in this yellow slice, so in this case, 
8.3%.

17
00:01:51.800 --> 00:01:55.001 align:center
